Cell.Text: [S] G|I thank you for your kindness.
[S] G|I understand. Some journeys must be taken alone. I'll be here if you change your mind.

Node.Caption: T03MauriceDontFollowResponse: I'd rather not have company right now.

Cell.Text: I am a traveler. A pilgrim. I follow the voice of Kynareth wherever it can be heard. | I've dreamed of seeing Eldergleam for years. Might I travel alongside you? I promise not to get in the way.
I had no idea you were a man of violence. What exactly are your intentions in this blessed place?
I had no idea you were a woman of violence. What exactly are you intending to do here?

Cell.Text: You would violate this marvel of Kynareth's glory to fix that half-breed stump in Whiterun? | That's abominable. Barbaric. I'll have no part of this. Why didn't you tell me what you intended?

Node.Caption: T03MauriceReactToPlan: I need sap to fix the Gildergreen.

Cell.Text: Well... yes. There is something. | It won't repair the tree back at the temple, but we could bring them a new one.

Node.Caption: T03MauriceHasAPlan: Do you have a better idea?

Cell.Text: [S] G|Follow me. I think I can convince the tree to help us.

Node.Caption: T03MauriceFollowMeToTree: What did you have in mind?

Cell.Text: [S] G|Very well. I can't stop you. But I can't bear to watch it, either.

Node.Caption: T03MauriceDisgust: I'll just take the sap. Danica was very insistent on having it.

Cell.Text: [S] G|With pleasure. Nature has a way of finding vengeance, though. You walk a bleak path, friend. One that will lead to suffering.

Node.Caption: T03MauriceWarning: Then stand aside. I have work to do.

Cell.Text: [S] G|I understand. Some journeys must be taken alone. I'll be here if you change your mind.

Node.Caption: T03MaurceUnderstanding: I'd rather not have company right now.

Cell.Text: Was I correct in hearing that you were traveling to the grove of the Eldergleam?
The Eldergleam has blessed us with a sapling.
[S] You should take it to Whiterun. Danica will want to see that the true blessings of nature lie in renewal, not a slavish maintenance.
I believe I'll stay here and bask in Eldergleam's warmth a bit longer.
It was my pleasure, friend. In a way, I envy you getting to carry such a direct sign of Kynareth's graces.
G|Good luck on your travels. May Kynareth's wind carry only the sweetest scents.
